public class ExampleCustomEvent extends CustomGameEvent
This is an example of a custom event. This is used to show how to create a custom event.

    • read

      public static ExampleCustomEvent read(Map<String,Object> configMap, GameEvent baseEvent)
      This is used to read the event from the config file. It takes in a Map object and a base game event. Data is not flattened in the config file, so keys will match the write function, with sub keys (and their corresponding maps) for nested data.
      Parameters:
      configMap - The Map object that contains the data for this event.
      baseEvent - The base event that contains the data that is common to all events.
      Returns:
      The ExampleCustomEvent that was read from the config file.

    • readSQL

      public static ExampleCustomEvent readSQL(Row row, GameEvent baseEvent)
      This is used to read the event from the SQL database. It takes in a Row object, which is a flattened form of the data in the database. This allows for easy access to the data, key for key basically.
      Parameters:
      row - The Row object that contains the data for this event.
      baseEvent - The base event that contains the data that is common to all events.
      Returns:
      The ExampleCustomEvent that was read from the database.
